delinquent /dɪˈlɪŋkwənt/

(delinquents) 

1. ADJ Someone, usually a young person, who is delinquent repeatedly commits minor crimes. (尤指青少年) 累犯的 

例： ...homes for delinquent children. …少管所。 

2. N-COUNT Delinquent is also a noun. 少年犯 

例： ...a nine-year-old delinquent. …一名9岁的少年犯。 

3. ADJ A delinquent borrower or taxpayer is someone who has failed to pay their debts or taxes. (债款、税款等) 拖欠的 [美国英语] 

例： ...a legal shortcut to take homes from delinquent borrowers. …一个取得拖欠贷款者房产的法律捷径。

